      <div purpose="report-section" id="part-1">
        <span purpose="section-marker">PART 1</span>
        <h1 class="pt-2">State of device management</h1>
        <p>Not only has technology enabled employees to work through laptops, smartphones, tablets, and other mobile devices, the shift to remote work has increased the need for it. More devices means greater risk of compromise and organizational security threats. This results in an increased need for endpoint visibility and monitoring.</p>
        <p>Our respondents told us about their current state of device management: what MDM they use, what devices they’re managing, and what they’re struggling to cover.</p>
        <div class="d-flex flex-row justify-content-center">
          <div class="d-flex flex-column col-6 pl-0">
            <h3>58% use a cloud MDM</h3>
            <p>The majority of our respondents (57.6%) use a cloud solution, hosted by a vendor, for their MDM. The rest are self-managed, and hosted by their organization.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="d-flex flex-column col-6 pr-0">
            <h3>They’re split on paying per user and paying per device</h3>
            <p>Just over half of our respondents (50.4%) pay per device, while the remainder pay per user.</p>
