      <div purpose="report-section" id="part-2">
        <span purpose="section-marker">PART 2</span>
        <h1>Best practices and challenges</h1>
        <p>Our respondents are directly involved in managing devices for their organization, which can be as many as 250,000 or more. Are they finding success in their efforts, or are they being derailed by daily inconveniences?</p>
        <p>Here are some of the best practices our respondents suggest for device management, and some of the challenges they face each day.</p>
        <div purpose="subsection" class="row">
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <img src="/images/icon-laptop-">
            <h3>Having a documented BYOD policy in place</h3>
            <p>With the rise in employees using their own devices for work, respondents say it’s imperative to have a documented policy over usage and access.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <img src="/images/icon-">
            <h3>Measuring point-in-time compliance across all devices</h3>
            <p>It’s a struggle to accurately monitor devices if you’re getting lagging or stale data. Another best practice is to ensure that you’re measuring compliance in real time across all of your devices.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <img src="/images/icon-">
            <h3>Reporting how quickly vulnerable software is patched</h3>
            <p>Another best practice is reporting, and keeping track of how quickly vulnerable software is patched so you can gauge response time and optimize for performance.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <img src="/images/icon-">
            <h3>Providing users a self-service experience</h3>
            <p>Respondents also see value in having end users be able to troubleshoot their issues themselves, instead of having to get IT involved.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <img src="/images/icon-">
            <h3>Focusing on a seamless end user experience</h3>
            <p>Finally, respondents stress having a solution in place that is seamless on the end user side, allowing for easy access and continued productivity.</p>
          </div>
